# Generated parsers / compiler output
build/
target/
*.o
*.so
*.dylib

# Published stable compiler binary for downstream app teams.
# Pinned via scripts/publish-stable.sh; lives outside git so the
# in-flight refactor cycle on `target/release/aperio` doesn't
# churn it underneath consumers.
/bin/

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/
*.swp
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Working notes (untracked by default; promote to notes/ when stable)
.scratch/

# Rust build artifacts
/target/
# Cargo.lock IS committed (binary workspace, reproducible builds).

# mdbook build output. Each doorway (and the archived book)
# builds under its own dir.
docs/**/book/

# Aperio app build artifacts (binaries + generated content)
apps/*/main
apps/*/out/

# Multi-file-seed binaries take the directory name as the output
# (apps/ferryman/ → apps/ferryman/ferryman). Match per app
# directory; the .ap-source files are explicitly preserved.
apps/ferryman/ferryman
apps/reload-demo/reload-demo
apps/market-book/market-book
apps/ws-echo/ws-echo
apps/cli-demo/cli-demo

# Aperio example build artifacts (compiled binaries sit next
# to main.ap after `aperio build`).
examples/*/main
# Multi-file examples take the directory name as the output —
# match per example directory the way apps/ does.
examples/14-projection-classes/14-projection-classes

# Codegen test fixtures build binaries next to their .ap sources
# (same `aperio build` shape as apps/ and examples/). Match the
# per-fixture-dir output: either `<dirname>/main` (single-file
# fixtures) or `<dirname>/<dirname>` (multi-file fixtures).
crates/aperio-codegen/tests/fixtures/**/main
crates/aperio-codegen/tests/fixtures/examples/05-bus/05-bus
crates/aperio-codegen/tests/fixtures/import-fallible-consumer/import-fallible-consumer

# Ferryman recognition output. Lands in <repo>/.ferryman/ wherever
# ferryman is pointed; the apps/operational-graph/fixture path
# is the in-repo smoke-test target.
.ferryman/

# experiments/token-efficiency lives on its own branch
# (experiments/token-efficiency). When that branch isn't checked
# out the dir still sits on disk; ignore its generated state so
# main's `git status` stays clean. Source files (briefs, tasks,
# harness, judges) are tracked on the branch, not here.
experiments/token-efficiency/.venv/
experiments/token-efficiency/workdirs/
experiments/token-efficiency/harness/runs.db
experiments/token-efficiency/.todo_storage*
**/__pycache__/
